Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Uncertain Tax Positions Under FIN 48:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: Junior Achievement of Greater New Orleans, Inc. and The Junior Achievement of Greater New Orleans Education Foundation, Inc. are nonprofit organizations exempt from income taxes under provisions of the Internal Revenue Service Code Sections 501(c)(3), respectively, and the Louisiana Revised Statutes; therefore, no provision has been made for federal and state income taxes. Junior Achievement applies a "more-likely-than-not" recognition threshold for all tax uncertainties. This approach only allows the recognition of those tax benefits that have a greater than 50% percent likelihood of being sustained upon examination by the taxing authorities. As a result of implementing this approach, Junior Achievement has reviewed its tax positions and determined there were no outstanding, or retroactive tax positions with less than a 50% likelihood of being sustained upon examination by the taxing authorities, therefore the implementation of this standard has not had a material effect on Junior Achievement. Junior Achievement's tax returns for the years ended 2009 and 2008 remain open and subject to examination by taxing authorities. The Company's tax return for 2010 has not yet been filed as of the report date.
